@startuml Seq05_DashboardReports
!theme plain
participant User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Dashboard\nAPI" as Backend
participant "Analytics\nEngine" as Analytics
participant "MySQL DB" as DB
participant "Chart Library\n(Recharts)" as Charts

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **LOAD DASHBOARD**

User -> Frontend: Navigate to Dashboard
Frontend -> Frontend: Show loading skeleton
Frontend -> Backend: GET /dashboard?period=current_month

Backend -> DB: Query transactions, budgets, goals
Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND date >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 30 DAY)
DB --> Backend: [30 transactions]

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM categories
DB --> Backend: [11 categories]

Backend -> DB: SELECT SUM(amount) FROM transactions\nGROUP BY category_id
DB --> Backend: [category totals]

Backend --> Frontend: {summary_data, period: "month"}

Note over Frontend: Frontend State Update:
Note over Frontend: totalSpent: 5420
Note over Frontend: transactionCount: 30
Note over Frontend: topCategory: Food
Note over Frontend: budgetStatus: 85%

Frontend -> Frontend: Render dashboard
Frontend --> User: Display dashboard

Note over User,DB: **DISPLAY SUMMARY CARDS**

Frontend -> Frontend: Render Card Component

Note over Frontend: Card 1: Total Spent
Note over Frontend: ₹5,420
Note over Frontend: 30 transactions

Note over Frontend: Card 2: Budget Status
Note over Frontend: ₹7,500 / ₹8,000
Note over Frontend: 93.75%

Note over Frontend: Card 3: Savings Progress
Note over Frontend: ₹2,100
Note over Frontend: Goal: ₹10,000 (21%)

Note over Frontend: Card 4: Financial Health Score
Note over Frontend: 72 / 100
Note over Frontend: Excellent

Frontend --> User: Cards rendered

Note over User,DB: **EXPENSE PIE CHART (BY CATEGORY)**

Backend -> Analytics: generate_expense_breakdown()

Analytics -> DB: SELECT category_id, SUM(amount) as total\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY category_id
DB --> Analytics: {Food: 2100, Transport: 980,\nBills: 1340, Entertainment: 600}

Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate percentages
Analytics -> Analytics: Food: 38.7%, Transport: 18.1%,\nBills: 24.7%, Entertainment: 11.0%

Analytics --> Backend: {pie_data: [...]}

Backend --> Frontend: {chart_type: "pie", data: [...]}

Frontend -> Charts: <pie data>
Charts -> Charts: Render pie chart
Charts --> Frontend: SVG pie chart
Frontend --> User: Show pie chart with colors

Note over User,DB: **EXPENSE BAR CHART (TOP MERCHANTS)**

Backend -> Analytics: generate_top_merchants(limit=10)

Analytics -> DB: SELECT merchant, SUM(amount) as total\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY merchant\nORDER BY total DESC\nLIMIT 10
DB --> Analytics: [McDonald's: 650, Amazon: 520,\nStarbucks: 380, ...]

Analytics -> Analytics: Format for bar chart
Analytics --> Backend: {bar_data: [...]}

Backend --> Frontend: {chart_type: "bar", data: [...]}

Frontend -> Charts: <bar data>
Charts -> Charts: Render bar chart
Charts --> Frontend: SVG bar chart
Frontend --> User: Show top 10 merchants

Note over User,DB: **MONTHLY TREND LINE CHART**

Backend -> Analytics: generate_monthly_trends(months=6)

Analytics -> DB: SELECT DATE_FORMAT(date, '%Y-%m') as month,\nSUM(amount) as total\nFROM transactions\nGROUP BY month\nORDER BY month
DB --> Analytics: [Jan: 5100, Feb: 5850, Mar: 4920,\nApr: 6200, May: 5420]

Analytics -> Analytics: Prepare chart data

Analytics --> Backend: {line_data: [...]}

Backend --> Frontend: {chart_type: "line", data: [...]}

Frontend -> Charts: <line data>
Charts -> Charts: Render line chart with 6-month trend
Charts --> Frontend: SVG line chart
Frontend --> User: Show spending trend

Note over User,DB: **MONTHLY REPORT GENERATION**

User -> Frontend: Click "Generate Monthly Report"
Frontend -> Backend: GET /reports/monthly?month=2026-05

Backend -> Analytics: generate_report(month=2026-05)

Analytics -> DB: Query all data for May 2026
DB --> Analytics: transactions, categories, budgets

Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate metrics
Note over Analytics: Total Spent: 5420
Note over Analytics: Budget Usage: 67.75%
Note over Analytics: Categories: 8
Note over Analytics: Avg Transaction: 180.67
Note over Analytics: Largest Expense: 420 (Flight)
Note over Analytics: Savings Rate: 32.5%

Analytics --> Backend: {report_data}

Backend --> Frontend: {month: "May 2026",\nsummary: {...},\nbreakdown: {...}}

Frontend -> Frontend: Format report
Frontend --> User: Display monthly report

Note over User,DB: **EXPORT REPORT**

User -> Frontend: Click "Export PDF"
Frontend -> Frontend: Generate PDF content

Note over Frontend: PDF includes:
Note over Frontend: - Summary cards
Note over Frontend: - All charts
Note over Frontend: - Detailed breakdowns
Note over Frontend: - Insights

Frontend -> Frontend: Download PDF
Frontend --> User: Report downloaded

alt Export CSV
    User -> Frontend: Click "Export CSV"
    Frontend -> Frontend: Convert data to CSV
    Frontend -> Frontend: Download CSV file
    Frontend --> User: CSV downloaded
end

@enduml
